---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BlogLikeButton from '../../components/BlogLikeButton.astro';
import BlogSubscribeCTA from '../../components/BlogSubscribeCTA.astro';

const keywords =
	'dark pop, dark pop project, cinematic dark pop, experimental pop, independent artist, music production, emotional songwriting, FHUGAWZ, AXIOMS, album diary, production diary, demo reconstruction';
const excerpt =
	'A first note on building a dark pop project from fracture, memory and proof, and on how a difficult experience can become songs, visuals and artistic direction.';
---

<Layout
	title="Fhugawz — Building Axioms"
	description={excerpt}
	spanishTitle="Construyendo AXIOMS: Dark Pop, Memoria y Reconstrucción Emocional | FHUGAWZ"
	spanishDescription="Una primera nota sobre construir un proyecto dark pop desde la fractura, la memoria y la prueba, y sobre cómo una experiencia difícil puede transformarse en canciones, imagen y dirección artística."
	keywords={keywords}
	image="/images/blog/building-axioms/building-axioms-dark-pop-origin-hero.webp.webp"
>
	<section
		class="page-hero with-image blog-article-hero"
		style={`--page-hero-image: url("/images/blog/building-axioms/building-axioms-dark-pop-origin-hero.webp.webp")`}
	>
		<div class="site-shell">
			<p class="section-kicker" data-i18n="post.building.kicker">PROJECT DIARY</p>
			<h1 class="page-title" data-i18n="post.building.title">BUILDING AXIOMS</h1>
			<p class="lede" data-i18n="post.building.lede">{excerpt}</p>
		</div>
	</section>
	<section class="section">
		<article class="site-shell article">
			<p data-i18n="post.building.intro.one">
				AXIOMS began as a way to give shape to things that were too heavy to explain directly.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.intro.two">
				Some experiences do not become clearer when you describe them literally. They become
				clearer when they turn into rhythm, image, pressure, silence and voice. That is the place
				where this album started.
			</p>

			<div class="article-image">
				<img
					src="/images/blog/building-axioms/building-axioms-argentina-night-memory.webp.webp"
					alt="Night city atmosphere connected to the emotional origin of AXIOMS."
					loading="lazy"
					decoding="async"
					data-i18n-alt="post.building.image.one.alt"
				/>
			</div>

			<h2 data-i18n="post.building.darkPop.heading">WHY DARK POP</h2>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.darkPop.one">
				Dark pop made sense because it can hold contradiction. It can be beautiful and
				uncomfortable at the same time. It can sound cinematic, fragile, aggressive, intimate and
				damaged without needing to explain itself too much.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.darkPop.two">
				For AXIOMS, that language became the right container for nostalgia, grief, desire,
				distance and survival. The goal was not to make sadness decorative. The goal was to turn
				it into something with structure, identity and emotional force.
			</p>

			<h2 data-i18n="post.building.fracture.heading">THE PERSONAL FRACTURE BEHIND THE ALBUM</h2>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.fracture.one">
				Part of this project comes from a personal rupture that happened around 2020, during a
				period marked by immigration, uncertainty, physical pain, recovery and emotional collapse.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.fracture.two">
				At the time, I was living in Argentina, far from Venezuela, trying to build stability
				while everything around me felt unstable. There were accidents, medical consequences,
				operations, prosthetics, pain, medication, recovery and the strange feeling of having to
				rebuild your body, your routine and your sense of self at the same time.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.fracture.three">
				Inside that process, other fractures also appeared: love ending when you are already
				broken, the feeling of being alone in a city that can be beautiful and brutal at once, and
				the need to keep moving even when the body and the mind feel exhausted.
			</p>

			<div class="article-image">
				<img
					src="/images/blog/building-axioms/building-axioms-fhugawz-studio-process.webp"
					alt="FHUGAWZ studio process while building the AXIOMS dark pop project."
					loading="lazy"
					decoding="async"
					data-i18n-alt="post.building.image.two.alt"
				/>
			</div>

			<h2 data-i18n="post.building.sound.heading">TURNING EXPERIENCE INTO SOUND</h2>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.sound.one">
				AXIOMS does not try to document everything literally. It transforms those experiences
				into songs.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.sound.two">
				The album moves through urban nights, emotional pressure, broken promises, toxic bonds,
				memory, rupture and the moment where a person decides not to disappear inside what
				happened to them.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.sound.three">
				That is why the songs are not only about sadness. They are about what remains after
				sadness. They are about the proof that something survived.
			</p>

			<h2 data-i18n="post.building.exists.heading">WHY THIS PROJECT EXISTS</h2>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.exists.one">
				This album is also a personal statement about building something professional without
				waiting for perfect conditions.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.exists.two">
				Not every artist starts with a perfect studio, a perfect budget or a perfect situation.
				Sometimes the only thing you have is a strong idea, discipline and the patience to shape
				the work carefully until it becomes real.
			</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.exists.three">
				FHUGAWZ exists from that place: music, visuals and production built as one emotional
				world.
			</p>

			<div class="article-image">
				<img
					src="/images/blog/building-axioms/building-axioms-emotional-reconstruction.webp"
					alt="Visual fragment representing emotional reconstruction inside the AXIOMS album world."
					loading="lazy"
					decoding="async"
					data-i18n-alt="post.building.image.three.alt"
				/>
			</div>

			<p data-i18n="post.building.closing.one">AXIOMS is the first open door into that world.</p>
			<p data-i18n="post.building.closing.two">
				Follow the project, listen to the previews and stay close to the process. More songs,
				lyrics, notes and visual pieces will keep unfolding from here.
			</p>
			<footer class="article-footer">
				<BlogLikeButton slug="building-axioms" />
				<BlogSubscribeCTA id="building-axioms-subscribe" />
			</footer>
		</article>
	</section>
</Layout>
